Oct 10 2009 	Very pleased-great value	We stayed from 9/26/09-10/2/09. Got a great deal on Orbitz. We arrived about 10:30 AM at the hotel. Room was not ready, so we walked around a bit, and had lunch, and by that time (about 12:30), it was ready(which was great because I belive check in time was 3 PM). We were on the 33rd floor with a view of the entire strip and mountains. It was fabulous! The room was the most spacious we have had in Vegas (previously stayed in Mirage and Bally's). The bathroom is very large with 2 sinks, separate shower stall and tub, and separate door for the toilet. The bed was very comfortable with nice pillows. Flat screen TV on the wall was very nice.We immediately went down to the pool, where it was very difficult to get a chair at that time, but we were not suprised because it was Sat. at 1:30 PM. The next day we had no trouble getting a chair. The pool was excellent.! The lazy river was really great! You could purchase an intertube for a little over $20, but we did not buy one, we just swam or floated, and it was a lot of fun. Also enjoyed the wave pool.I went to the gym inside the Spa. I was pleased that it was only $20/per person per day, instead of $30 that I had read elsewhere (it is $30 if you want to use their whirlpool and locker room). In addition, it was $45 for a 3 day pass for gym only, which I purchased. I felt this was a fair price because they had a lot of cardio equipment in the gym, so there was no problem getting to the machines, and bottled water also was included. They do also have a windy path that I think is a quarter mile outside the pool area that you can run on for free, but I didn't attempt it.The hotel has some good reasonable places to eat. There was a very good 2 for 1 breakfast at the House of Blues. We also ate at Border Grill (Mexican) and Cafe Giorgio (Italian), both were moderately priced with good food. There was a special at the buffet were you could have breakfast, lunch, and dinner for $35/day per person, but we did not do it because we had activities planned outside the hotel. When we went to other hotels for these activites, we noticed the Mandelay Bay is more spacious/less crowded and quieter than other hotels. Did go to the Shark Reef inside the hotel, which we felt was worth the $17/per person.The only negative I could say is it takes abour 1 hours to get down the strip from the hotel, even with the monorail. They have a tram from Mandelay Bay that you can take for free to Excalibur. You then walk to MGM Grand which takes another 10 minutes. Once inside MGM Grand you have to walk all the way through their casino and their mall to get to the monorail which takes about 15 minutes. Overall though, we would definitely consider staying again next time we plan a trip to Las Vegas!	
