Sep 27 2009 	The best hotel in Las Vegas to unwind	Beautifully maintained and appointed hotel, excellent rooms and public facilities but best of all, away from the noise and hurly burly of the main part of the Strip. Staff were very helpful and polite. Restaurants varied from cheap quick burger to haute cuisine. The casino was large and airy and the machines well spaced out, and unlike most other hotels it wasn't the first thing you saw before you registered. Pool area was busy but generally beds were available (pick your spot early). We don't have a bad thing to say about Mandalay Bay and would definitely stay there again.Travel tips - catch the free shuttle to Las Vegas Outlet Centre, the Deuce ($3 single) downturn or the free monorail and then the low cost tram to cover the whole of the Strip. LV is very accessible for those who require a little extra help getting around.	
