Sep 25 2009 	Great hotel though a little far off	We had been to Vegas 4 different times, so we knew exactly going into the trip that the Mandalay Bay, though on the strip is a little far off. However since I got comped a few free nights and got a cheap rate the others, we figured to give it a shot. We normally stay more in the middle of the strip but figured with the tram to Excalibur it shouldn't be a big deal to get to the rest of the strip. First off the check in was a breeze, I had read it takes a long time, so it might just be when we arrived but the entire process from once we walked in the door to getting the keys, took about 5 minutes max. We had a view that was overlooking the pool (I won't post pics since it was done about 80 times already) and our cousins had a view overlooking the mountains (not as nice). We did request a king size bed and were given two full/queen's, but who cares. As longs as they gave me a bed I was fine. The room is very nicely appointed and the cleaning crew did a great job getting in whenever we took the privacy sign down. We had no trouble at all getting an elevator ever. I read that this is an issue, and we stayed on the 10th floor and can't remember waiting more than 30 seconds for one. We have eaten two good meals here in the Border Grill and The Burger Bar, both were excellent and the Burger Bar might have been the best burger I ate in years. The casino was not very crowded, but they did keep the table minimum's up higher than almost any other hotel (including the Bellagio), not sure why but due to that I donated less to them than I would have, since I didn't play as long. We did have an incident at this hotel and needed to deal with security. The first person we dealt with was terrible, would barely help us and was rude. The next day the security staff was much nicer, however the first experience left a bad taste in our mouth. The location was another negative, if it's your first time in Vegas stay more in the center. Due to the heat we didn't like to walk to much so ended up taking more cabs in 3 days there than I had in all my other trips combined. If it wasn't so hot we would have just taken the tram to Excalibur and walked but it being over 100 for 2 of the 3 days made that experience an uncomfortable one. We did have an issue with our bill checking out as they comped my cousins room and not mine, and it did take them about 15 minutes to straighten it out, but they eventually did. It was an inconvenience but what can you do. As for the best part, the pool area. When we go back in warm weather months we will definitely stay at this hotel just for the pool area. We did buy two tubes at home and brought them there, and they do pump it up for free so that was a nice feature. We spent time on the lazy river and it was not crowded at all and was absolutely fantastic. I guess since school just got back in session the families stayed away. I also went to the wave pool, it was OK, nice feature but more for kids I guess. They also had two other normal pools. Overall I don't know how you can make this place better. We spent hours here and wish I could have stayed a few more days just to chill on the lazy river.Overall this is a very nice hotel, its upscale but not overly pretentious. It has some very good places to eat, it's big so there is always someplace else to explore. Is it a little far from the main part of the strip, yup, so take that into account. I would definitely stay here again during the months I could use the pool, however when it cooled off I would not just because of the location.	
