Aug 4 2009 	Always a nice stay....	This was my 4th time in as many years staying at the Mandalay Bay. The rooms are plenty big enough. Bathroom is large with 2 sinks, seperate tub and shower, and seperate toilet. Bathroom also has a small tv in case you need a tv fix while getting ready.The pool area is great but very busy. We found that the south lagoon pool was virtually empty while all others were packed, the reason being is that it is tucked away by itself. Eventually it will get busier as the afternoon progresses but if you were down to pool by 11am it was pretty easy getting a chair.Enjoyed the great buffet deal offered at Bayside Buffet. Pay $35 and you get to have a breakfast, lunch, and dinner at the buffet. If you know you are going to be hanging out Mandalay and like buffet food this is a screaming deal. Food was very good with crab legs, prime rib, and shrimp on the dinner buffet.Enjoyed Orchid Lounge which had a great band playing ( I believe it is their house band).Only a couple of minor downsides, first is location at far end of strip, but since I go to Vegas about 3 times a year I didnt feel the need to wander to far. Secondly is their checkin, they have no stanchions so it is a free for all, you are praying you pick the right line. I only had one person in front of me and their checkin took over 25 mins (not checkin agents fault, just happened to get one of those people that had to ask a million questions). Other than those two things if you like nice rooms and a great pool, and some good nightlife then check this place out.	
