Mar 23 2009 	If this is a 5 star resort Las Vegas must use their own rating system	The Mandalay Bay Resort and Casino is a 5 star resort which is reflected in the price. Was I disappointed?...absolutely. In general the carpets are dirty, light fixtures are broken or not working and the furniture in the room is beat up. The whirlpool tub in the room hasn't been cleaned in a while and there is bacteria visible in the jets. We booked a suite for 3 people and found out when we arrived that they would be charging us extra for a cot. When we booked a room for 3 people wouldn't it be logical to expect sleeping arrangements for everyone in the room? This hotel is at the end of the strip and not exceptionally busy. If you are looking for action or night life this is not for you. The pool and beach area are nice especially if you have kids.	
Mar 18 2009 	Nice hotel front desk staff not very accomodating	I stayed at this hotel back in Nov for a trip with my mum and our package came with an upgrade. On arrival I found the check in staff very aloof and unfriendly, just what you need after a 10hr flight! We were promised a non smoking room with 2 double beds but there weren't any available so we had to share a bed (that took me back to my childhood!) That was the only downside as everything else was great and contrary to other reviews I found the housekeeping staff brilliant and probably the friendliest of all the Mandalay staff. The rooms are so clean, our towels and sheets were replaced daily and our rooms were left immaculate. Fast forward to March 09. My husband and I stayed at the Mandalay this time also. Again, I felt really disappointed with the check in staff. Maybe it was bad luck, but once again I found the staff very rude. I booked an upgrade prior to the trip, and on arrival there wasn't anything available. To be honest apart from a few extra feet space, there isn't much difference betweebn a 550dr or 750dr room as you still get the same amenities and room service (apart from a spa tub). I requested bath robes on both trips and both times I didn't get them. Just a minor gripe, but these little things all add up. On arrival to our room,our room safe was locked and after 4 calls to the front desk and 2 hours of waiting, someone eventually arrived to unlock it only to find the previous guest's stash of drugs in there! The housekeeping staff were really happy and friendly towards us (maybe it's all of the leftover drugs!). Even if we had a lie in and didn't leave our room until quite late in the day, our room was still cleaned for our return. The spa was fantastic but like other reviewers, I think the cost should be included in the room charge and I also don't think that guests should be expected to pay $30 a day for the use. The House of Blues happy hour menu runs from 3pm - 6pm (i think) and the food is tasty and reasonably priced although the only alcohol available on the happy prices is beer. We had a great meal at the Border Grill (mexican) and The Burger Bar in Mandalay Place. The queue for the Shark Reef was sooo long and yes it was nice but too small a place to cram so many people into, so I wouldn't say that &quot; you really must visit it.&quot; The tram was out of action for the whole of my 2nd stay and I really missed it as it really helps out with all of that walking that you will need to do. We got around by using the deuce bus as I think the cabs are a rip off and the bus is a great way to see the strip. It costs $3 one way or $7 for a 24 hr ticket and they run every 10mins. Don't expect to get anywhere fast though as it can take an hour to get through the strip. The traffic, amount of stops and the numbers of passengers can make it a long journey. Get a seat upstairs at the front and you can take in the sites and help pass the time. You would never catch me going upstairs on a London bus as it's too intimidating, but these buses are great fun and the fellow passengers are all in high spirits. For shopping, I'd recommend getting off at Denny's at the end of the strip to catch the 108 deuce bus to Las Vegas Premier Outlets. On my first trip we spent $60 in cab fare there, but you live and learn! Also, the deuce bus to Fremont St is a great experience, but go of a night time to see the light show and the street entertainers. We had a fab meal at Lille's Chinese Restaurant in the Golden Nugget Hotel in Fremont and I would highly recommend it. We saw the shows KA at the MGM and Phantom at the Venetian, both fantastic, but I got better and cheaper tickets by booking my tickets in London. I used tix 4 tonite (next to the giant cola bottle on the strip) to buy my phantom tickets as they were advertising great offers, but you have to get there early in the morning to get the best tickets and expect to queue. Saying that, I did and I still paid alot to sit right at the back (where I was told I was sitting and where I sat were completely different areas of the theatre) as you are not told your seats no's until you collect your tickets from the hotel box office. The official sites are doing some great offers at the moment. We had two great meals at the Paris Hotel. The cafe in the Paris do a great breakfast and we had a lovely steak meal in Mon Ami Gabi, both highly recommended. One final word of warning if staying at the Mandalay Bay. DON'T use the phone in your room. The room tariffis are very misleading. The only info in the room on rates is that all direct calls are charged at standard rate. Therefore I made 5 calls to London totalling no more than 2 mins each and on checking out, I was presented with a bill for $256! I was really angry as I felt like I 'd been completely ripped off. I paid and then went back to my room to call reception and complain as I didn't want to cause a scene in the lobby and this time finally spoke to someone who was actually pleasant and approachable. She understood my gripe and put me on hold for a while. She came back to me and agreed to wave all charges and credited the bill back to my card which I wasn't expecting. I didn't actually end up paying anything at all, which is great but it still left a bad taste to think that they could try and do that to a guest. I've stayed here twice now and would stay next time at the Wynn, Bellagio or the Venetian as these seem to have great reviews, but if you have booked the Mandalay, you won't be disappointed, and Vegas is a fab place, you'll have so much fun!	
